    <h1>On so&#xAD;cial me&#xAD;dia</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200930/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-30"><time>2020-09-30</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE TRENDING</span>
        - <span role="byline">PHOTO: CHRISSY TEIGEN/IN&#xAD;STA&#xAD;GRAM</span>
    </section>

    <p>MRS JOHN LEG­END HOS­PI­TALISED: Model and TV per­son­al­ity Chrissy Teigen, 34, has been hos­pi­talised after suf­fer­ing heavy bleed­ing dur­ing her preg­nancy.</p>
    <p>Teigen, who is ex­pect­ing her third child, a boy, with singer hus­band John Leg­end, was taken to Cedars-Si­nai Med­i­cal Cen­ter in Los An­ge­les on Sunday.</p>
    <p>She shared pho­tos of her­self and her hos­pi­tal stay on In­sta­gram and Twit­ter, as­sur­ing fol­low­ers that she is do­ing all right, de­spite her preg­nancy com­pli­ca­tions.</p>
    <p>“About to have my se­cond blood trans­fu­sion which truly truly truly sounds more dra­matic than it is. It’s an IV, but in­stead of flu­ids, the blood of some kind hu­man be­ing out there,” she wrote in a cap­tion ac­com­pa­ny­ing an In­sta­gram post in which she is wear­ing a New Year’s 2020 party favour on her head (above).</p>
    <p>Teigen has two other chil­dren, Luna, four, and Miles, two.</p>
    <p>She has been open about her preg­nancy strug­gles, with both of her pre­vi­ous preg­nan­cies con­ceived through in-vitro fer­til­i­sa­tion.</p>

